## Constraints

- Design interface first, implementation second.
- Every public function must survive the deletion test: if callers could trivially implement it, don't expose it.
- No more than 7 public functions. If the design exceeds 7, split the module.
- One error type per module. Map, don't leak, dependency errors.
- One config struct. Validated at construction.
- Hide everything that isn't required by callers.
- Do not execute arbitrary Python code in Jinja2 expressions (sandboxed execution).
- Handle missing variables gracefully (leave as-is or use default if specified).

